"Je suis un mauvais garçon!"


258
00:18:08.309 --> 00:18:09.861
Oh.

259
00:18:32.546 --> 00:18:35.655
Hey, Gru,
whatcha doing down here?


260
00:18:35.656 --> 00:18:37.417
In the dark.

261
00:18:37.418 --> 00:18:38.362
Alone.

262
00:18:38.363 --> 00:18:41.205
Oh nothing, just thinking.

263
00:18:41.206 --> 00:18:42.675
You okay?

264
00:18:42.676 --> 00:18:45.352
Oh yes, yeah,
I'm fine, I'm fine.


265
00:18:45.353 --> 00:18:47.296
It's just…

266
00:18:47.513 --> 00:18:53.198
I don't know.
I guess I just feel like a… failure.


267
00:18:53.387 --> 00:18:55.707
Like I don't have
a purpose anymore.


268
00:18:55.708 --> 00:18:59.237
Hey, mister,
you are not a failure.


269
00:18:59.238 --> 00:19:02.768
If only I could've nailed Bratt.

270
00:19:02.782 --> 00:19:06.193
So many times I almost had him!

271
00:19:06.194 --> 00:19:08.758
But now I'll never
get the chance.


272
00:19:08.759 --> 00:19:10.882
'Cause I have been
kicked to the curb.


273
00:19:10.883 --> 00:19:14.547
Gru, you've got to let this go.
It's time to look forward.


274
00:19:14.548 --> 00:19:17.396
Things will get better, I promise.

275
00:19:38.917 --> 00:19:40.890
- Uh, excuse me.

276
00:19:40.949 --> 00:19:44.558
Pardon me,
young... people.


277
00:19:44.559 --> 00:19:47.949
Would you tell me
how to get to this address?


278
00:19:51.245 --> 00:19:53.637
I'm looking for a Mr. Gru.

279
00:20:06.586 --> 00:20:08.505
Idiots.

280
00:20:11.527 --> 00:20:13.724
No. Kyle.
Stop!


281
00:20:13.725 --> 00:20:15.963
Kyle, let go.

282
00:20:18.145 --> 00:20:19.419
BRATT STEALS WORLD'S
BIGGEST DIAMOND


283
00:20:19.420 --> 00:20:22.617
No, no...
you've got to be kidding me.


284
00:20:22.618 --> 00:20:23.796
Lucy, did you see...

285
00:20:23.797 --> 00:20:27.673
He helps you if you have nightmares,
and he's really good to snuggle with...


286
00:20:27.674 --> 00:20:29.416
Oh no, no, no, Agnes!
Agnes!


287
00:20:29.417 --> 00:20:31.630
So, take good care of him.

288
00:20:31.631 --> 00:20:33.356
Thank you!

289
00:20:33.357 --> 00:20:36.024
Agnes, what are you doing?
You...


290
00:20:36.025 --> 00:20:37.904
You sold your unicorn?

291
00:20:37.905 --> 00:20:42.237
Well, I just wanted to help.
Since you don't have a job.


292
00:20:42.419 --> 00:20:44.916
I got two whole dollars for it!

293
00:20:44.941 --> 00:20:47.055
- Awwwww.
- Awwwww.


294
00:20:47.647 --> 00:20:49.417
Uh, excuse me.

295
00:20:49.418 --> 00:20:51.552
Sorry, buddy, the sale's over.

296
00:20:51.553 --> 00:20:53.022
Yes, but this will only take a....

297
00:20:53.047 --> 00:20:55.576
Hey, Eyebrows.
Get off the lawn.


298
00:20:55.601 --> 00:20:56.976
Yeah, but...

299
00:20:56.977 --> 00:21:00.377
- Hey, could you...
- Oh uh, of course.


300
00:21:00.378 --> 00:21:02.776
Now, as I was saying.
I...


301
00:21:02.777 --> 00:21:05.603
- Uh... Oh.
- Goodbye.


302
00:21:10.883 --> 00:21:13.433
Listen, Agnes.
You don't need to worry.


303
00:21:13.434 --> 00:21:15.259
We're going to be fine.

304
00:21:15.260 --> 00:21:17.537
- For real?
- For real.


305
00:21:17.538 --> 00:21:19.360
Now come on,
let's pack this stuff up.


306
00:21:19.385 --> 00:21:20.581
Ow.
Ow.


307
00:21:20.606 --> 00:21:24.127
Seriously?
Buddy, you're not getting the hint.


308
00:21:24.128 --> 00:21:26.885
Excuse me, Mr. Gru.

309
00:21:26.886 --> 00:21:30.245
But I really must
have a word with you.


310
00:21:30.246 --> 00:21:31.835
How did you know my name?

311
00:21:31.836 --> 00:21:36.287
Allow me to introduce myself...
my name is Fritz, and OW!


312
00:21:36.288 --> 00:21:38.574
Uh, good puppy.

313
00:21:38.575 --> 00:21:43.102
And I am inquiring…
on behalf of your twin brother, Dru.


314
00:21:43.103 --> 00:21:44.629
He needs your help.

315
00:21:44.630 --> 00:21:46.397
What?
Twin brother?


316
00:21:46.398 --> 00:21:47.488
Twin brother?

317
00:21:47.489 --> 00:21:48.529
- Twin brother?
- Twin brother?


318
00:21:48.530 --> 00:21:49.447
Oh Yeah.

319
00:21:49.448 --> 00:21:52.927
He would like to fly you
to Freedonia to meet him.


320
00:21:52.928 --> 00:21:56.832
Your father has recently
passed away and...


321
00:21:56.833 --> 00:21:59.748
Okay, cuckoo.
I'm sorry, but my dad died


322
00:21:59.749 --> 00:22:02.408
when I was a baby,
and I don't have any brother.


323
00:22:02.409 --> 00:22:03.767
You've got the wrong guy.

324
00:22:03.768 --> 00:22:04.975
Really?

325
00:22:04.976 --> 00:22:09.803
Well, then how do
you explain... this?


326
00:22:15.287 --> 00:22:18.537
Ahhhhh!
Bellissimo!


327
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:23.316
- Oh, hello, Gru.
- Hi, Mom.


328
00:22:23.317 --> 00:22:27.865
It's important to keep active
in one's golden years.


329
00:22:28.670 --> 00:22:32.221
There you are, you cute cute.

330
00:22:34.658 --> 00:22:41.243
These are my diving instructors,
Vincenzo and Paolo!


331
00:22:41.781 --> 00:22:44.106
Ciao, boys!

332
00:22:44.107 --> 00:22:46.263
So what do you want?

333
00:22:46.264 --> 00:22:49.883
Mom, do I have a twin brother?

334
00:22:50.234 --> 00:22:52.305
How did you find out?
Who told you?


335
00:22:52.306 --> 00:22:53.776
Wait, what?
It's true?


336
00:22:53.777 --> 00:22:55.890
You never told me
I had a brother!


337
00:22:55.891 --> 00:22:59.443
And you told me that Dad died of
disappointment when I was born!


338
00:22:59.444 --> 00:23:03.008
Yeah, yeah, that was the agreement.

339
00:23:03.009 --> 00:23:06.685
Agreement?
What are you talking about?


340
00:23:08.849 --> 00:23:14.438
Shortly after you and your brother
were born, your father and I divorced.


341
00:23:14.439 --> 00:23:17.783
We each took one son
to raise on our own.


342
00:23:17.784 --> 00:23:21.882
And promised never
to see each other again.


343
00:23:22.757 --> 00:23:27.864
Obviously, I got second pick.

344
00:23:29.708 --> 00:23:32.273
I have a brother.

345
00:23:38.686 --> 00:23:41.519
Hey girls, how are things
in row B, huh?


346
00:23:41.520 --> 00:23:44.089
I've put together some
fun activities for the trip.


347
00:23:44.090 --> 00:23:47.094
Who is up for some Gin Rummy?

348
00:23:47.095 --> 00:23:50.980
Yeah. Umm...
We're good.


349
00:23:50.981 --> 00:23:52.880
Oh.
Okay.


350
00:23:52.881 --> 00:23:55.542
I'll just sit here
and play solitaire.


351
00:23:55.543 --> 00:23:57.442
I hope I win.

352
00:23:57.891 --> 00:24:00.029
I wonder what Dru will be like!

353
00:24:00.030 --> 00:24:00.499
Woo!

354
00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:02.293
Maybe we'll have that twin thing

355
00:24:02.294 --> 00:24:05.364
where we can read
each other's minds, you know?


356
00:24:05.365 --> 00:24:09.327
- How cool would that be?!
- Um, super cool.


357
00:24:16.049 --> 00:24:18.887
Ah, ha ha ha...

358
00:24:18.888 --> 00:24:20.837
Ooh.

359
00:24:22.579 --> 00:24:24.588
Aah!
Ow! Ow!


360
00:24:24.589 --> 00:24:26.128
Woo-hoo!

361
00:24:26.129 --> 00:24:30.588
Freedonia!
Freedonia!


362
00:24:30.803 --> 00:24:32.673
Hi, piggy, piggy!

363
00:24:32.674 --> 00:24:36.135
Huh! Whoa!
Look at that house!


364
00:24:36.136 --> 00:24:37.785
It's like a castle!

365
00:24:37.786 --> 00:24:41.825
I can't wait to meet my brother!

366
00:24:41.826 --> 00:24:44.032
Uh.
What's with all the pigs?


367
00:24:44.033 --> 00:24:46.392
This is the family business.

368
00:24:46.393 --> 00:24:50.474
The largest pig farm
in the whole of Freedonia.


369
00:24:50.759 --> 00:24:53.269
Okay, nice pig.

370
00:24:53.481 --> 00:24:56.391
No!
That's my private part!


371
00:24:56.392 --> 00:24:58.669
Owww!

372
00:24:58.670 --> 00:25:01.385
This pig has issues!

373
00:25:01.575 --> 00:25:03.059
Please, come in.

374
00:25:03.060 --> 00:25:05.489
Wow.
Yeah, haha!


375
00:25:11.392 --> 00:25:13.043
Whoa!

376
00:25:13.044 --> 00:25:16.029
Oh, this is amazing!

377
00:25:16.030 --> 00:25:20.402
Ah, it's like the Sistine Chapel.
But with pigs.


378
00:25:24.127 --> 00:25:31.941
My brother!!

379
00:25:31.942 --> 00:25:33.685
- My brother!
- My brother!


380
00:25:33.686 --> 00:25:34.944
Gru!

381
00:25:34.945 --> 00:25:36.866
Dru!

382
00:25:42.910 --> 00:25:48.467
Ahhhh!
Brother! I am hugging you!


383
00:25:48.468 --> 00:25:50.565
I'm so happy!

384
00:25:50.655 --> 00:25:55.074
After all these years,
finally I'm meeting you!


385
00:25:55.075 --> 00:25:59.047
- Yup, alright, good.
- Oh, look at that!


386
00:25:59.048 --> 00:26:01.277
- Woo!
- You must be the beautiful wife!


387
00:26:01.278 --> 00:26:04.458
Beautiful, oh.
Stop it!


388
00:26:04.459 --> 00:26:05.264
Sweet talker.

389
00:26:05.265 --> 00:26:09.360
How is my brother finding a wife
like you when he is so bald?


390
00:26:12.223 --> 00:26:16.484
Woo-hoo!
These must be my nieces!


391
00:26:16.485 --> 00:26:20.281
Huh! You're Agnes,
you're small with big eyes!


392
00:26:20.282 --> 00:26:22.525
And it makes me want to
put you in my pocket!


393
00:26:22.526 --> 00:26:25.917
You can't do that.
I'm too big.


394
00:26:25.942 --> 00:26:27.524
And Edith,

395
00:26:27.525 --> 00:26:31.014
I can tell that you are
a little mischievous.


396
00:26:31.015 --> 00:26:33.655
We're going to have to make
a little trouble later.


397
00:26:33.656 --> 00:26:35.380
Wha...
I already have!


398
00:26:35.381 --> 00:26:37.081
Ow.
Ow! Ow!


399
00:26:37.082 --> 00:26:39.749
Please, stop.
Why are you doing that?


400
00:26:39.750 --> 00:26:41.140
Ow!
Ow.


401
00:26:41.141 --> 00:26:44.616
Fist bump for mischievous behavior.

402
00:26:44.617 --> 00:26:47.643
And Margo!
Oh, you are so mature.


403
00:26:47.644 --> 00:26:50.490
I'm guessing what… fifteen?

404
00:26:50.491 --> 00:26:51.718
Fifteen?

405
00:26:51.719 --> 00:26:55.361
She's twelve! She looks twelve.
And will always be twelve.


406
00:26:55.362 --> 00:26:58.473
So, Dru… this place is amazing.

407
00:26:58.474 --> 00:27:02.241
I mean, you just walk through the doors
and you're like: wooooowwwooowwooooo!!


408
00:27:02.242 --> 00:27:07.969
Eh. It's nice, I guess, sure.
I'm not really into 'things.'


409
00:27:10.334 --> 00:27:12.451
Wow!
This is so cool!


410
00:27:12.452 --> 00:27:14.816
Oh my gosh,
he's even got a helicopter!


411
00:27:14.817 --> 00:27:16.948
This is the best!

412
00:27:16.949 --> 00:27:19.274
Yes, the best.

413
00:27:19.275 --> 00:27:21.654
- All right, let's go home now.
- Home? Why?


414
00:27:21.655 --> 00:27:25.329
I don't know, this guy,
with the mansion and the cars


415
00:27:25.330 --> 00:27:30.106
and… all the hair,
silky-smooth, luxurious hair.


416
00:27:30.107 --> 00:27:32.496
I feel worse than
I did before I came.


417
00:27:32.497 --> 00:27:35.300
Oh, but he's your brother, Gru.
Give this a chance.


418
00:27:35.301 --> 00:27:38.972
Oh, I was thinking, while Gru and I
catch up on some brother stuff,


419
00:27:38.997 --> 00:27:41.699
you girls should go with Fritz.
He has a surprise for you.


420
00:27:41.700 --> 00:27:42.956
- Yay!
- Yay!
- Awesome.


421
00:27:42.957 --> 00:27:44.261
I love surprises!

422
00:27:44.262 --> 00:27:46.493
Oh, this is perfect.
Mother, daughter bonding time.


423
00:27:46.494 --> 00:27:48.832
Let's do it.
Woo-woo!


424
00:27:48.833 --> 00:27:51.194
Bye!
You boys have fun.


425
00:27:51.195 --> 00:27:54.430
Ha ha ha!
Whoopee!


426
00:27:56.759 --> 00:27:59.164
Now you can be as evil
as Balthazar Bratt


427
00:27:59.165 --> 00:28:01.644
with the evil Bratt action figure,

428
00:28:01.645 --> 00:28:05.392
featuring music activated
Break Dance mode.


429
00:28:05.393 --> 00:28:09.691
Also featuring bubble gum
launching shoulder pads.


430
00:28:09.692 --> 00:28:13.732
And the all new
Mega Diamond Laser.


431
00:28:15.251 --> 00:28:16.933
No more math!

432
00:28:16.934 --> 00:28:19.927
I've been a bad boy!

433
00:28:20.520 --> 00:28:23.797
The Mega Diamond Laser does not
actually incinerate books.


434
00:28:24.449 --> 00:28:29.774
How could Hollywood cancel a show
that produced toys like this, Clive?


435
00:28:29.897 --> 00:28:32.318
Evil Bratt was a masterpiece.

436
00:28:32.319 --> 00:28:34.928
Does no one value
true art anymore?


437
00:28:34.929 --> 00:28:37.101
It's a disgrace and a travesty, sir.

438
00:28:37.102 --> 00:28:41.067
Well, now that I've got the diamond,
it's payback time.


439
00:28:41.068 --> 00:28:44.978
Oh, it's too bad Gru won't be
around to try and stop me.


440
00:28:44.979 --> 00:28:47.596
Oh, wait! No, it's not!
I hate that tweeb!


441
00:28:47.621 --> 00:28:49.549
And you, Hollywood!

442
00:28:49.550 --> 00:28:52.783
This time, I'm canceling you!

443
00:28:52.784 --> 00:28:56.239
And all the losers
who rejected me!


444
00:28:56.240 --> 00:28:58.782
Ha ha ha...!

445
00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:06.610
So how are things
going for you, career-wise?


446
00:29:06.611 --> 00:29:08.437
Ahhaaaaa… great.

447
00:29:08.438 --> 00:29:11.443
So, so great.
Crushing it.


448
00:29:11.444 --> 00:29:18.044
Well, I've got something that I think
you will find very interesting.


449
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:22.033
Hold on to your face, Brother.

450
00:29:26.636 --> 00:29:27.965
Whaaaaaaaaaa!

451
00:29:39.507 --> 00:29:41.082
Ow!

452
00:29:50.553 --> 00:29:53.850
- Whoa. Whoa.
- Come on, come on.


453
00:29:55.618 --> 00:29:57.794
What is all this?

454
00:29:57.795 --> 00:30:02.739
The pig farm was just a cover
for the real family business.


455
00:30:04.482 --> 00:30:05.880
Haha!
Hey.


456
00:30:08.812 --> 00:30:12.846
Now, feast your eyes on…

457
00:30:12.847 --> 00:30:18.243
Dad's lair!
Ta-da!


458
00:30:18.244 --> 00:30:23.883
Whoa whoa whoa, wait…
So our dad was a villain?


459
00:30:23.884 --> 00:30:26.195
No, no, no.
Not just a villain.


460
00:30:26.196 --> 00:30:29.782
But one of the greatest
of all time!


461
00:30:29.783 --> 00:30:34.050
He was known as the Bald terror.

462
00:30:34.051 --> 00:30:37.259
That's him?
Our dad?


463
00:30:37.260 --> 00:30:41.526
He was so proud of you.
And what a great villain you were.


464
00:30:41.527 --> 00:30:42.910
He was?

465
00:30:42.911 --> 00:30:46.257
But me… not so much

466
00:30:46.258 --> 00:30:51.891
To Dad, I was just a failure.

467
00:30:51.892 --> 00:30:54.884
He never thought I had
what it took to be a villain.


468
00:30:54.885 --> 00:30:58.752
But now you can help me
prove him wrong.


469
00:30:58.753 --> 00:31:03.744
Brother, teach me the art of villainy!

470
00:31:05.025 --> 00:31:08.283
No. No, no, no.
I can't do that.


471
00:31:08.284 --> 00:31:13.251
What? But it's our family tradition!
You can't say no to that!


472
00:31:13.252 --> 00:31:16.803
Look, I'm sorry.
I've left that life behind me.


473
00:31:16.804 --> 00:31:19.477
- End of story.
- Oh.


474
00:31:20.117 --> 00:31:22.607
Okay.
I understand.


475
00:31:22.608 --> 00:31:25.535
Hmmm… I wonder what this does?

476
00:31:41.860 --> 00:31:43.253
Holey moley!

477
00:31:43.254 --> 00:31:48.230
Dad's villain wheels.
Pretty slick, huh?


478
00:31:48.231 --> 00:31:50.654
Hey, you want to
take her out for a spin?


479
00:31:50.655 --> 00:31:52.937
Just for some fun?

480
00:31:53.658 --> 00:31:56.101
Hmmmmm…

481
00:31:56.533 --> 00:32:00.262
Woo-hoo!

482
00:32:00.949 --> 00:32:02.719
Look out!
Whoa! Whoa!


483
00:32:02.720 --> 00:32:05.346
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

484
00:32:06.070 --> 00:32:07.987
What a beautiful day!

485
00:32:07.988 --> 00:32:12.463
Zero to 400 in 3 seconds.
Able to withstand a nuclear blast,


486
00:32:12.464 --> 00:32:14.847
armed to the teeth!

487
00:32:15.996 --> 00:32:18.357
Oh yeah.
That's pretty nice.


488
00:32:18.358 --> 00:32:22.156
- And it's a hybrid.
- LOOK OUT!


489
00:32:42.768 --> 00:32:46.161
Yeah!
Help me!


490
00:32:47.753 --> 00:32:52.192
I am not enjoying this...!

491
00:33:00.629 --> 00:33:02.846
Whoa.
What is going on here?


492
00:33:02.847 --> 00:33:06.790
Welcome to the annual
Freedonian Cheese Festival!


493
00:33:06.791 --> 00:33:08.167
Go!

494
00:33:12.409 --> 00:33:16.321
Ooo. Look. Look.
Look at all the candies!


495
00:33:16.437 --> 00:33:18.263
Whoa!

496
00:33:18.854 --> 00:33:21.553
Lucy, can we get these please?

497
00:33:21.554 --> 00:33:24.220
Okay, but only one each.
I mean it.


498
00:33:24.221 --> 00:33:26.289
- Awww.
- Oh, man.


499
00:33:26.290 --> 00:33:28.672
No, I don't!
Get as many as you want,


500
00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:30.141
